article.headline: Polk, Wheeler score 23 each for Wildcats
article.linkText: Arizona ties school record 10th straight victory
article.story:
TUCSON, Arizona (Ticker) -- Shawntinice Polk and Dee-Dee 
Wheeler each scored 23 points to lead No. 25 Arizona past
Arizona State, 81-60.

Polk, who entered the contest leading the team in scoring with
17 points per game, scored 23 points on 10-for-17 shooting and
grabbed 10 rebounds for the Wildcats (11-2, 3-0 Pac-10), which
has tied a school record with 10 straight wins.

Wheeler, a sophomore from Chicago, netted her 23 points on
9-for-14 shooting from the floor for Arizona, which shot 57
percent en route to its school-record 21st consecutive home win.

Danielle Adefeso chipped in with 14 points and senior Aimee
Grzyb added nine points, including the 1,000th of her career for
the Wildcats, who will travel to Baton Rouge to face No. 17 LSU
on Sunday, January 4th.

Emily Westerberg missed just two shots and scored a team-high 21
points for the Sun Devils (8-4, 2-1), who fell to 36-29
all-time against Arizona.

Kristen Kovesdy netted 10 points for Arizona State, which had
won six of its last seven games, losing a non-conference
showdown with No. 1 UConn.
